{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}} <!-- {{Copyedit|date=November 2010}} --> {{Infobox software | name = ClipGrab | title = ClipGrab | screenshot = | caption = | released = {{Start date and age|2007|11|05|df=yes}} | latest release version = 3.7.1 | latest release date = {{Start date and age|2018|10|03|df=yes}} | genre = [[Download manager]] | operating system = [[Microsoft Windows]], [[Mac OS X]], [[Linux]] | language = English, German, French | license = [[GPL v3]] ([[free software]]) | website = {{url|http://clipgrab.org}} }} '''ClipGrab''' is a multi-platform software for downloading videos from popular websites such as [[YouTube]], [[Vimeo]], [[Dailymotion]] or [[Metacafe]]. It also provides the possibility to convert the downloaded files to other file formats such as [[MP3]], [[MPEG4]], [[OGG Theora]] or [[WMV]]. It is published as [[free software]] under the terms of version 3 of the [[GNU General Public License]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://git.clipgrab.org/ClipGrab/blob/master/COPYING |title=ClipGrab Git COPYING |publisher=Philipp Schmieder |date=12 August 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402123804/http://git.clipgrab.org/ClipGrab/blob/master/COPYING |archivedate=2 April 2015 }}</ref>
== Features == ClipGrab officially supports the download from a handful of video websites which include YouTube, Collegehumor, Dailymotion, Vimeo. In addition to this, the software provides a [[heuristic]] which can also download videos from sites that are not officially supported. When available, ClipGrab offers different quality options for a video. With this feature, the user can choose between downloading a [[High-definition video|high definition]], standard definition or low definition version of the video. ClipGrab can automatically detect compatible URLs when they are copied to the clipboard. The program also provides an integrated search function for YouTube. It has been especially praised for its clean and easy-to-use user interface.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.tagesspiegel.de/medien/digitale-welt/gewusst-wie-videos-von-youtube-auf-der-festplatte-speichern/1677922.html |title = German newspaper "Der Tagesspiegel" recommends ClipGrab |work = tagesspiegel.de |date = 6 February 2010 |language = German }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.thewindowsclub.com/clipgrab-download-convert-videos-youtube-vimeo-dailymotion |title = Review by The Windows Club |work = thewindowsclub.com |date = 10 November 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.chip.de/downloads/ClipGrab_40171753.html |title = Review by the Chip Magazine |work = thewindowsclub.com |date = 18 November 2011 }}</ref> Software review site softoxi.com states that "[ClipGrab] has a beautifully designed graphical user interface" and "stands out immediately for its look, feel and performance"<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.softoxi.com/clipgrab.html |title = Review by softoxi.com |work = softoxi.com |date = 24 November 2011 }}</ref>
